The paper deals with deep learning methods for image restoration, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new framework for controlling the latent features of the network, which involves learning coupling coefficients and providing finer control of the restored image quality. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions experiments on several typical image restoration tasks, which suggests that it may be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR).
